Qwen3.6 ModelOpt mixed NVFP4 (W4A16_NVFP4) support — upstream PR #27906.
MAINAHEAD VARIANT — regenerated against SGLang tag v0.5.14.

Target model: nvidia/Qwen3.6-35B-A3B-NVFP4 (modelopt MIXED_PRECISION checkpoint:
W4A16_NVFP4 MoE experts + shared-expert linears + lm_head, FP8 attention/linear_attn).

Why a separate file from sglang-qwen36-mixed-nvfp4-pr27906.patch:
  PR #27906 is still OPEN upstream, but v0.5.14 NATIVELY merged the modelopt_mixed
  BASE (class ModelOptMixedPrecisionConfig in modelopt_quant.py) that the original
  (v0.5.13-rebased) patch assumed it was adding context around. The ONLY real
  conflict vs v0.5.13 is cosmetic: upstream dropped the forward-ref quotes on the
  ctor annotation (`nvfp4_config: "ModelOptFp4Config"` -> `nvfp4_config:
  ModelOptFp4Config`), so Hunk #7 ("add nvfp4a16_config param + assignment")
  failed to apply. v0.5.14 still LACKS the W4A16_NVFP4 path itself (no
  ModelOptNvFp4A16LinearMethod, no nvfp4a16 routing), so this patch is still
  required for the Qwen3.6 model.

  This file is regenerated wholesale against the v0.5.14 tag (git diff over the
  applied tree) so every hunk lands zero-fuzz; the v0.5.13 recipes keep the
  original sglang-qwen36-mixed-nvfp4-pr27906.patch. Selected automatically by
  build_sm121_image.sh when the recipe sets SGL_KERNEL_MAINAHEAD=1 (installed
  under the canonical name).

What it adds (unchanged from the original; see that file's header for full notes):
  - configs/model_config.py: detect MIXED_PRECISION with real NVFP4 / W4A16_NVFP4.
  - modelopt_quant.py: nvfp4a16_config plumbing + a dedicated
    ModelOptNvFp4A16LinearMethod (NVFP4 weight-only / W4A16, Marlin, group_size=16)
    and routes W4A16_NVFP4 Linear/LMHead/MoE to it.
  - logits_processor.py / vocab_parallel_embedding.py / weight_utils.py: wrapper-
    prefix + lm_head handling.
  - models/qwen3_5_mtp.py + speculative/eagle_worker_v2.py: MTP wiring.

NB: still pairs with the dispatch fix PR #28099 (also OPEN) — see the model
profile + reference_qwen36_nvfp4_modelopt_mixed. Re-validate on the live model
after building (NVFP4 quant path); drop this patch once #27906 lands in the
pinned SGLANG_REF.

Upstream source: sgl-project/sglang tag v0.5.14 (PR #27906 rebased)

